    64	## Review Status
    65	
    66	### Round 0 — findings addressed
    67	
    68	- **Bug — §5.3 replay after work/* pruning.** Fixed in
    69	  `integrator.py::_check_idempotent`. The manifest-bytes check no
    70	  longer depends on the worker commit being alive — it now reads
    71	  the committed trial commit's tree and manifest blob directly.
    72	  The tree-shape re-verification (§3.2 invariant) is now
    73	  conditional on `commit_exists(trial.commit_sha)` being true, since
    74	  §1.3 explicitly permits work/* cleanup. New regression test
    75	  `TestIdempotentReplayAfterWorkerPruned` runs `git gc
    76	  --prune=now` between integrations and asserts the second call is
    77	  a no-op.
    78	- **Bug — non-finite floats in metrics / manifest JSON.** Fixed in
    79	  two layers: `_base.py::_validate_metrics` now rejects non-finite
    80	  floats for `real` metrics via `math.isfinite()`; `_manifest.py`
    81	  sets `allow_nan=False` on `json.dumps` as defense in depth. New
    82	  test `TestNonFiniteMetricsRejected::test_nan_metric_rejected_at_integration`
    83	  seeds a trial with `float("nan")` and asserts
    84	  `NotReadyForIntegration`.
    85	- **Risk — dispatch → real integrator coverage gap.** Fixed by
    86	  `test_end_to_end_with_real_integrator` in
    87	  `eden-dispatch/tests/test_end_to_end.py`. The test builds a real
    88	  `GitRepo` in `tmp_path`, pre-creates three `work/*` branches,
    89	  seeds the scripted implementer to return the real SHAs/branches,
    90	  wires `Integrator.integrate` into `run_experiment`, and asserts
    91	  the `trial/*` refs exist, the subject lines match §3.3, and the
    92	  `trial.integrated` events land.
    93	
    94	All 339 tests pass. ruff / pyright / markdownlint / spec-xref clean.
    95	
    96	### Round 1 — findings addressed
    97	
    98	- **Bug — §5.3 replay silently accepted corrupt tree after
    99	  worker prune.** You reproduced this by rewriting the stored
   100	  trial/* commit to a tree with an extra file but the same
   101	  eval.json, deleting work/*, and running `git gc --prune=now`;
   102	  the second `integrate()` accepted it as no-op. I agree that
   103	  skipping the tree check when the worker commit is pruned is
   104	  too permissive — §5.3's no-op path requires the tree to
   105	  satisfy §3.2, and without the worker tree we cannot prove
   106	  that. Fixed in `integrator.py::_check_idempotent`: when the
   107	  worker commit is no longer reachable, the integrator now
   108	  raises `CorruptIntegrationState` rather than silently
   109	  treating the replay as a no-op. Updated regression test
   110	  `TestReplayAfterWorkerPruned::test_replay_after_worker_gc_raises_corrupt_state`
   111	  confirms this. New test
   112	  `TestCorruptTrialTreeRejected::test_tree_with_extra_path_rejected`
   113	  exactly reproduces your scenario (extra file in trial/* tree
   114	  with the same eval.json, work/* still present) and asserts
   115	  `CorruptIntegrationState`.
   116	
   117	Deployment consequence: a deployment that wants §5.3 replay
   118	idempotence after eager work/* cleanup must either retain the
   119	worker commit/tree via a separate anchor ref, or accept that
   120	replay after cleanup surfaces as `CorruptIntegrationState`
   121	requiring operator intervention. This is the literal §5.3
   122	reading; a looser reading (trust §1.2 to protect against
   123	external writers, skip tree re-verification) is permissible in
   124	a conforming third-party impl but the reference impl takes the
   125	strict reading.
   126	
   127	### Round 2 — awaiting review.

